<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_cævæg" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>cævæg</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>коса (орудие)</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>scythe</q></cit></sense><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_cævæg." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>jæxīcæn nyssaʒy ysqælfynʒ cævæg</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>налаживает себе косу со вздернутым концом</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>[he] sets up a scythe with an upturned end</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>56</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>cævægæj, ... æxsyrfæj cættæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>коса, ... серп наготове</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>scythe, ... reaping hook are ready</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>124</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><re><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>cævægqæd</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>cævægǧædæ</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>древко косы</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>shaft of the scythe</q></cit></sense><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>sawdortæ cævæg insunmæ, cævægǧædtæ...</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>оселки („черные камни“) для точки косы, древка косы...</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>touchstones (‘black stones’) for wheting the scythe, shaft of the scythe</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>245%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit></re><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>jæxīcæn nyssaʒy ysqælfynʒ cævæg</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>налаживает себе косу со вздернутым концом</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>[he] sets up a scythe with an upturned end</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>56</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>cævægæj, ... æxsyrfæj cættæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>коса, ... серп наготове</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>scythe, ... reaping hook are ready</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>124</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Лексикализованное причастие на -%iæg%i от глагола <xr><ref target="#entry_cævyn"/></xr> ‘бить’, собственно „бьющее“ или „секущее“ орудие. Ср. по образованию <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>šalga</w><gloss><q>коса</q></gloss></mentioned> %bшорск%b. , буквально „бьющее (орудие)“ от <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>šal-</w><gloss><q>бить</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/><gloss><q>ударять</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl corresp=""><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Грамматика шорского языка, стр. 28</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">The grammar of Shor, p. 28</biblScope></bibl>); Развитие значения ‘бить’ → ‘косить’, как в немецком <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>hauen</w><gloss><q>бить</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="de"><w/><gloss><q>ударять</q></gloss></mentioned>, , — <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>Gras hauen</w><gloss><q>косить траву</q></gloss></mentioned>. — Из осетинского (аланского) усвоено в западнокавказские языки: <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>šāmāg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-crc"><lang/><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><w>čämäg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="abq"><lang/><w>čbəg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/><w>ā-čbəga</w><gloss><q>коса</q></gloss></mentioned>. См. <xr><ref target="#entry_cævyn"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>313, 336</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">A lexicalized past participle with the suffix -%iæg%i of the verb <xr><ref target="#entry_cævyn"/></xr> ‘beat’, in fact “beating” and “cutting” tool. Cf. by the derivation <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>šalga</w><gloss><q>scythe</q></gloss></mentioned> %bшорск%b. , literally “beating (tool)” from <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>šal-</w><gloss><q>beat</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/><gloss><q>hit</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl corresp=""><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Грамматика шорского языка, стр. 28</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">The grammar of Shor, p. 28</biblScope></bibl>); The development of the meaning ‘beat’ → ‘scythe’, like in German <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>hauen</w><gloss><q>beat</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="de"><w/><gloss><q>hit</q></gloss></mentioned>, , — <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>Gras hauen</w><gloss><q>cut the grass</q></gloss></mentioned>. — The word was borrwed by West Caucasian languages from Ossetic:<mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>šāmāg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-crc"><lang/><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><w>čämäg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="abq"><lang/><w>čbəg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/><w>ā-čbəga</w><gloss><q>scythe</q></gloss></mentioned>. See <xr><ref target="#entry_cævyn"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>313, 336</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>